1953;;Laxdale Hall;;British;;John Eldridge;;Kathleen Ryan, Raymond Huntley;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laxdale_Hall;;A British parliamentary delegation is dispatched to the village of Laxdale - a loosely disguised Applecross - in the Scottish Highlands where the residents are protesting at their poor links with the outside world. After a few days amongst them, and initial problems of interaction, the visitors begin to fully appreciate the locals' lifestyle